' PlantUML example — Implementation layer: internal component breakdown of
' APPLICATION-OMS-1 and its interface to APPLICATION-CRM-1.
'
' Derived from:
'   - canon/views/applications/eu-portfolio.applications.transitrix.yaml
'       APPLICATION-OMS-1 -> APPLICATION-CRM-1, outbound REST, "Propagates order
'       and erasure events to CRM".
'   - canon/elements/02_business/processes/PROCESS-ORD-FULFILL-1.yaml
'       STEP-ORD-FULFILL-2 "Validate Order", STEP-ORD-FULFILL-4 "Pick and Pack".
'
' Not a duplicate of canon/views/c4component/application-containers.c4.md:
' that Mermaid C4 view stops at container level (APPLICATION-OMS-1 as one box).
' This diagram opens the container up into its internal components — detail
' one level below what C4Container is meant to show.

!include transitrix-theme.puml
@startuml OMS — component decomposition

package "APPLICATION-OMS-1 (Order Management System)" #f4f9fb {
  [Order Intake] as Intake #e8f2f5
  [Order Validation] as Validation #e8f2f5
  [Fulfilment Engine] as Fulfilment #e8f2f5
  [Event Publisher] as Publisher #e8f2f5
  database "Active-order DB" as DB #e8f2f5
}

interface "REST outbound" as CRMApi

Intake --> Validation : new order
Validation --> DB : persist
Validation --> Fulfilment : validated order (STEP-ORD-FULFILL-2)
Fulfilment --> DB : update status (STEP-ORD-FULFILL-4)
Fulfilment --> Publisher : order / erasure event
Publisher --> CRMApi
CRMApi --> [APPLICATION-CRM-1\n(CRM System)] #ccd8dc

@enduml
